---
title: Sticky Pork Mince Stir-Fry & Garlic Rice with Asian Greens & Slivered Almonds
description: A stir-fry sauce can do no wrong, in fact it’s perfection when cooked with veggie mince, creating lovely sticky flavours. There’s veggies and a fragrant garlic rice to absorb all the leftover sauce. It’s too good to miss!
We’ve replaced the crushed peanuts in this recipe with slivered
almonds due to local ingredient availability. It’ll be just as delicious, just follow your recipe card!
